    "The typical statistical measure for this comparison is the log-likelihood ratio (𝐺 2) value, computed as follows [9]:𝐺 2 = 2 × O 11 × ln O 11 E 11 + O 21 × ln O 21 E 21For our keyness analysis, we measure n-grams, with n ranging from 1 to 5.",
